        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="6">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This service procedure is for 9800 Models with 63, 89, and 110 inch cabs. Whenever cab length
                        is important to a step in this procedure, it will be noted in that step.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air intake transition pipe from chassis.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Flush the inside of the transition pipe with a power washer.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Shorten transition pipe 2-15/16 inches as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">63 inch cab length</emph>-Wrap masking tape around the transition pipe 2
                        inches from the 90 degree elbow on the end that enters the air cleaner housing. Install a second
                        wrap of masking tape around the transition pipe 2-15/16 inches from the first location. Cut this
                        2-15/16 inch section from the transition pipe (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790501">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790501" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790501" filename="../afcfigures/g9790501.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">89 inch cab length (excluding 89 inch cab with 37 inch extenders-refer to 100
                            inch cab)</emph>- While the air intake piping is still intact on the vehicle, wrap masking
                        tape 1-7/8 inches from the junction of the two transition pipes. Place a second wrap of masking
                        tape 2-15/16 inches from the first wrap of masking tape. Cut this section from the transition
                        pipe (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790502">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790502" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790502" filename="../afcfigures/g9790502.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <para>Flush the inside of the transition pipe with a power washer.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">110 inch cab length and 89 inch cab length with 37 inch extenders-</emph>Wrap
                        masking tape 7 inches from the air cleaner end of the transition pipe. Install a second wrap of
                        masking tape 9-15/16 inches from the air cleaner end of the transition pipe. Cut this 2-15/16
                        inch section from the transition pipe (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790503">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790503" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790503" filename="../afcfigures/g9790503.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <para>Flush the inside of the transition pipe with a power washer.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the moisture skimmer eliminator into the transition pipe. The air flow arrow on
                    the moisture skimmer eliminator must be pointing toward the air cleaner. Tighten the clamp screws to
                    11 to 14 in-lbs. (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790504">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9790504" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9790504" filename="../afcfigures/g9790504.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To prevent distortion of the air intake pipe, do not over tighten the screw clamps on the
                            moisture skimmer.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the 6 tinnerman nuts, bolts and washers on the vertical air intake
                    pipe and replace with new style tinnerman nuts, bolts and washers provided in the 8000790R91 kit.
                    Tighten bolts to 75 to 90 in-lbs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install intake pipe rubber sleeves:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">63 inch cab length</emph>-Apply silicone gasket material, Navistar Part Number
                        446839C1, to the slip joint grooves on the transition pipe. Install one rubber sleeve at the
                        joint between the transition pipe and the air cleaner housing. Install two rubber sleeves at the
                        transition pipe slip joint (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790505">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9790505" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9790505" filename="../afcfigures/g9790505.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>The 63 inch cab length requires 3 of the 4 rubber sleeves provided in the parts kit.
                                The 89 and 110 inch cabs require all 4 rubber sleeves.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <emph type="bold">89 and 110 inch cab length-</emph>Apply silicone gasket material, Navistar
                        Part Number 446839C1, to the slip joint grooves on the transition pipe. Install one rubber
                        sleeve at the joint between the transition pipe and the air cleaner housing. On all cab sizes,
                        install two rubber sleeves at the transition pipe slip joint (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9790505">Figure 5</hotlnk>). Install one rubber sleeve on the joint located at
                        the air inlet vertical pipe to the air inlet transition pipe next to the exhaust stack mounting
                        bracket.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>It is not necessary to install a rubber sleeve at the joint between the air inlet
                                vertical pipe and the air inlet snorkel.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the complete air inlet pipe system. Install the two bolts that mount the air
                    inlet snorkel to the exhaust mounting bracket. Tighten the bolts to 30 to 35 ft-lbs.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>On all cabs built before December, 1996, and re-using the original narrow sleeve, tighten
                            the bolts to 25 to 30 ft-lbs.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air cleaner housing cover and element.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the two 1/4 inch drain holes. Use these drain holes as a pilot and drill them out
                    to 1 inch diameter using an offset drill and hole saw (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790506">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9790506" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9790506" filename="../afcfigures/g9790506.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not remove the air cleaner housing to drill the new drain holes.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash the inside of the air cleaner housing with detergent to remove drilling chips and
                    contaminants.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two VAC valves in the 1 inch diameter holes at the bottom of the air cleaner
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9790506">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new air cleaner element provided in the parts kit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air cleaner housing cover.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
